ided with SDC is not a separate module but just a functionality which enhances the capabilities of the house keeping department. When the house keeping department notices something not working in a room such as the mini bar or the television, they notify the maintenance department regarding the nature of the defect filling out a form which is presented in the above figure under â€˜Send Response Requestâ€™. After receiving the task the maintenance department on the other hand mobilizes its crews to take the right course of action based upon the information that was passed from the house keeping. Upon completion of the task in hand the maintenance notifies the house keeping and only then the house keeping change the status of the room to its respective state. Below is a screen shot of the form from where the maintenance is notified. After filling out the appropriate fields shown above the task is sent to maintenance by clicking â€˜Dispatch to Maintenanceâ€™. When maintenance sees the task and completes it as requested, they resolve the task by clicking â€˜Set Resolved Timeâ€™ which marks the task as Resolved. Below is a screen shot of the Maintenance which can be accessed by clicking â€˜View Historyâ€™ in the figure above.',_binary '“NUMPY\0v\0{\'descr\': \'<f4\', \'fortran_order\': False, \'shape\': (384,), }                                                          \n€n±;\0Ù¼\õ‚\É<\Ë?r=/¨`=Ln;eˆ[=ce½9’<¥t!<\Æ4=œ…¼\Î\è\å<>\ò¢»y½Àº á¥¼\ó=ÿ\à\é¼\Æ}¸¼sZ.¼‰#°»(7F=b\ãJ<S\rƒ½¥8½¾r=*/\\<š\İv½T<\\ûR½O‹<\'¸˜=©µ=M\àw=\ñ\Ã=³6¦½~kx½Vq<½\å=\Ş\Ñ\ô¼¨	À½@<\åH½:(YO½‘@š½¦\ç\å<©\á½\ŞÙ¨½=\óˆ=Ÿ+t¼\èÿ\"<\rı=\ç\É=%Q\Í=v\ŞV=¯6`=¡«X=£&£½H3$½%g½G¨=SN]¼4\à2<\ì$œ:i=t]@<_6œ¼\îŒ½\ãd=Œw½fiX½r’=K{=\ôc=	\×d=1JË¼©Ç‡;\ç6½®C‡=SÖ½ı½·\Ç)½.Ñ½J\É =êŠ¼\Ï\Ü\Ì<\âLf½œ&½\÷h¦=\0½_Z<¶¯0=_2½ş¾½ı`\æ;AH6»+6½?³\Ï<sÆƒ<¾\ëù<5;”»6ü¦<LÁ½\ò?½œ\ñ½›7=»b<t\Ë<<w\İ)½M7Í½\İv<D=P\Õ19‚²¼\á\Ä\'<”M\ì=);~©Ø¼\÷zÃ¼:‘=Ü“½,‹V½\à\Ë\'½\'Ÿ =\0!(<\Ò=d©	 Nz=ı§½Kü½ø,;/\ö=¢á¼\à`®;%0;Æ¥=c\Ã