many different areas. Now let us go deeper into each of the modules of SDC. 2.2 Front Office. 2.2.1 Overview : The screen shot seen above is from the front office screen. Individual rectangles denote individual rooms of a hotel with their current status being represented by the color of these rectangles. For example, rooms 701 and 702 are out of order therefore they appear in a grey color, and the legend present in the right hand corner represents exactly just that. On the upper right hand corner there are 5 buttons. They are: 2.2.2 Refresh Button: Refreshes the display screen and updates the current house status. 2.2.3 Find Button: Upon entering guest room number in the highlighted textbox the user can press the Find button or press â€˜Enterâ€™ to view the room details. 2.2.4 Rates Button: Pressing the Rates Button will display the different rates offered in the hotel . Rates such as CP, MAP, BB can be seen with their individual breakdown of their room rates and meal plan rates. 2.2.5 View Report Button: Clicking on the View Report button, different reports can be seen. Details of different reports are covered in further sections. 2.2.6 Drop Down Menu Functions: Fig 2.2 Buttons Fig 2.3 Room State Fig 2.4 Room Type There are three Drop Down menus present in the front office screens which are highlighted above. The first one gives you the list of different room types present in the hotel such as Single, Double, Suite etc. The second one contains different room states as such Vacant, Out-of-order, Occupied etc. Selecting (Fig 2.5) different combinations of room states and room types and pressing the Find button or enter, the user can view the desired room having the selected states and types. For example in figure 2.2 and 2.3 user wishes to view all the single rooms in a hotel that are vacant. (Fig 2.5) Given below is a screen shot of the result where different room number and their corresponding states are seen. Fig (2.6) 2.2.7 View Room Button: In the above figure if one clicked room number 605 which is highlighted with the blue shade (indicating that the room is occupied), one would also be able to view the details of the room. The Figure is given below. 2.2.8 Reservation. Overview Fig (2.7) The figure above is from the Registration screen of the SDC. There are two types of reservations namely FIT Reservation and Group Reservation, which can be viewed by selecting the respective buttons shown below in figures 2.8 and 2.9. (FIT Reservation button or Group Reservation button). The result of the desired query can be seen',_binary '“NUMPY\0v\0{\'descr\': \'<f4\', \'fortran_order\': False, \'shape\': (384,), }                                                          \nF«—<-~v¼MY»½Áÿ§=’tt=\à¡\Ó=\ÏC<hV›½°9´=‹ÿ¼Z&O=x»^½l·½¾¼i¥2=\ñŠ`½\Ñ\n;jÍ‡½\ßü$<s 4<\É\Ö8<	{Â»r˜Á¼bbÂ¼\ôe¼\êaŸ<aY\Z½“ªM=Š\ó¼<ì·½ \Z\â<†¨µ=i+£=‰Cr=\ôA=F!½n\÷»\ë¼[\Õ=lù¼ˆ|r½u\"\Ò<Ğ¸Z¼F·»§½;ÿ\0<~½+l×¼u\ö0<\Ê={À=°\îP<ÁB½\ã’=^7ø<,±	>¬ƒÿ<f\ôÑ¼\×\Æ;]E\ß;\0*\Î<\Ê\Úl¼\ôœ<¨<›jL½+•=`ªÛ¼\äv=vÁ\';Ë¸-¾\\øŒ»\ê\ÆN<}0<<½\â\â\Ù<™—½7Ab½F¶ºq<‡\ñ½¾\Ü@½WJ=x*!¼v=˜›<^i˜<\çºE<ßœµ¼\àZ¹<\ÅÕ»F(Œ= \':•+¼\ÜÌ¼½k<P#:¼|B½ae=şÿ›=M\ä`¼”n1=ú´,=\ä\ôş<=¡¼Q_c<¿Î£½®\Æü=|\ß<A1\0½\Ã\çr»Ÿ´+½0r±=/¼%³¸½\ğÄ¢¼:@˜;ı,\é<\r»ÿ‡G=Z\ï.½\ğ—=\òq`¼dN¼:´g½\òK½·+u½\ÊH=Q\ãş	u¼&Ä–½#¢C½™Òª<\">\Ì&<\Â.¼\ĞÓ¸;\â_=o¬\Î<_e†<ı~œ=\ãš#½K ¥¼!¼\à2½ŒšJ¼Ö¸\ã=£bïº»†¦¼°&½©i(¼YY=\ÇÖ¼Á \Î=u^&>\ï_Ÿ=~\Ô=6\Ïû<s”;v;=™¡„»\ÕC=jc=Mù»<b{5=O» «	;H\è	<¤\×\Ç<\Ø(Á½Fm£»©k‘½»Q‚¼\ÊN£½Ÿm=\Ñ\nU=X\â¼<ŠQX=\èNq=Pÿj½\ï\Û(½ÀÜ§½\Æ]ê¼–QŠ<Ñ–Å½°^<œ•q¼\Æ5½5Q;“-=©c7=M\áA¼j=V^½\ñ\r=¼S½\ñˆâ¼³\"¹=\nüA½‰\Ç½&Sn¼/£[=¦:½\ï\à\İ;»>¤¼1fÏ¼e½¼X’½\Ôq\Ù;	½™½\"\Õ\Z½Ğ©½ŸŠ&=¦¼f\í¼\0pp=—ÿN»Z\Éå¼³Op½a\É½\İZ\r½“8.=¿*=¼ø\Ëş‰\ÆZ”=\Øq„¼\Ù\éS½ÙŠØ½\í[N½k\è‰9S\å¢<‰l<Ø³<\ÔÀ<v‘¡¼İŸ<<]\ò^½ š<*›P¼µSu=¢‘ˆ=*<l©Ü½r\'Á<wªd½Z\Û`={“¼7.\"½O\Ô|½±&\Ú=\æG[=\Î\Û\Ö;šú<t’½E\ã7½‰ƒ¯½*qı¼\Ñ0\Ö=°8[=P.-½ø<\r=³I½tj^½–h=‰\÷`=‡\Ô>¼0&Í½r„<.Š5¼U¼\Ø:Y=\Ñ<N+ı<ZÁÅ»šá‰½¼­\ì»\â7½Œ–½ EÄ¼!\ÒÕ½ú\Ğ\æ=\ï\Ê\æ:\ê\Ğd¼›º\Ï=€È©<–Ü¯»ú\ä¯<cµ;\óhƒ=\Ó}¦