onfirm the action. After clicking â€˜Yesâ€™ the bills are settled and now the check out procedure can be initiated. To go ahead with the check out procedure the billing instruction needs to be checked. If the billing instruction says â€˜Bill to Travel Agentâ€™ then â€˜TA Voucherâ€™ should be selected as the Payment Method. If â€˜Payment at Check Outâ€™ is the billing instruction then the amount, currency and mode (cash/credit card) needs to be entered. When the parameters entered are accepted by the system click â€˜Check-Out Groupâ€™ button. Upon clicking â€˜Yesâ€™ at the prompt the group is successfully checked out of the system and out of the hotel. 3.2 Point of Sale Functions 3.2.1 Start a Table The figure above is a screen shot of the main screen of the POS. The numbers on each of the green buttons represent a table number and the color represents its present state. To start a table one must click on the respective table where the current state is vacant. Upon clicking any of the vacant tables a prompt is generated for the server/manager password. After entering the passwords the system asks for the total number of guests being served on that table. Upon entering the required information and pressing â€˜Okâ€™, the ordering panel becomes available from where we can select the items that were ordered by the guest. After the ordering is complete the kitchen is to be notified hence the â€˜Sendâ€™ button needs to be clicked for the order to be sent to the kitchen. Below is a screen shot of the ordering panel. When the â€˜Sendâ€™ button is clicked, a printer placed in the kitchen prints the KOTâ€™s together with all the information such as the table number, ordering server, order time and order details in that KOT. The table status also changes from vacant to occupied. 3.2.2 Add more items to an existing Table To add more items to an existing table just click on the respective table to open it. When the ordering screen is screen after entering the right server password, select the items being ordered just as before by clicking their names on the screen and when youâ€™re done click â€˜Sendâ€™ for the kitchen to be notified. 3.2.3 Settle a Table',_binary '“NUMPY\0v\0{\'descr\': \'<f4\', \'fortran_order\': False, \'shape\': (384,), }                                                          \n\è\ák<7\á=\Ãxz½_<¼±¼\0Q¯»\Ì\Ë=\ïÂ¼™QQ=^(=\n|¹=) §½\Zz«<¨\"¼rf =–¬Ä½\åŒ2¼\ó­½°Á½½.l=~Jª»Q@¼lµ\\¼(t(½©#Î»\Ë$9¼††ü;[‘ºH7£<4\"+½•…=±\Ô\à=\Zd\Ü<\Óo„½\Ô\ô==\ñ\î\ë;\ó”¼Gk½kl—¼¢\è]<³\'½ÍŒ!½\ğ‹;\n\Çy½²\ôy=t[¥<\Ï\ã¼\çhp=ËŠ¼0\é}=£\Óf=\í8\í¼‘$<Q\Ò?=úÓ‘½I+‰;\è–=ƒ/¼Y:Q0ê½¼^L½º[ÿ<Š”J½,\İ0=E„½+\ÒL=\Å5\Í:ü8\n=U<WøP½E1\ë<E>=<sÈ=¹¬¼š¼¿9\í°=r\È¹\íZp9\Í=t’»\Ï\÷\Ë<¨\ã,½ü‘½Ö«›»5	„<`=½t\É½\Ôtüº—\ë\é;šc½\ğı= \Ö=¼);ˆø›½Äªª=\n\Ë9{½lŠn¼DÜ–=\0‘\Ñ:1F€=‘o\Ï<e@Ù¼^/½D\ä=O\n©¼Nt\Å=\î\è;8˜=\ñ$T½±>T½ Ld½?¸=‹\à½I½z­\ë=zK\È<Ø—c<Á=9®‡½q$F=s%=”~½\÷dº½*//=ƒ\"G=]\ß,=\àË›	\Şo¼|\r¡¼şøl½Y½û©=\ßC\n½\Õdß¼\õ\ÛU=À\ğ¿¼\ŞU\Z=\Â4Š¼OJÙ½\ñ5=\ê}½¥ˆ±½)\Ä9R\r½ı\ëC=”‹¼¸Cø=3\Ó;*Ë»pÀµ= À§=û‘N½ù\Æü=œ„¶<\òI«<t\à\å<j…¼X¡;=©q¶<úQ£<¾x¯=Û¯N½\â\ê¸=\å\Ú\Ù<\ód;q\ÄW=<\r1½²\ÌO¼.Ç¼\àw\ğ<(—†¼”\×7½r/H=®\äx¼9½1È=\ö’\Â=‡–€½KPR<e¿Ô½d\ì~»\õş\n½\ñfÃ½·º¼\÷\óG¼¡3­;0\Û^½~‰\Ù;\\e¶½„¹¼U§:O¦N½F·\à:q‹¼f\à1½\'A=ÁE½—Ø…½\Æ)R=Œ+>\Éh=\Éì¨¼È„z=^B+<M¨\n=yR5¼jb=úZ½ZK¼@TÀ:=¸;‰=)=:ˆ«<Œ›¼c‹¼\é ¼pšT¼\á\Åe»­W]º\ö¼\Ø@\é=sü­‰WQ\Ó<“b=+¹™½Z^;Ó¨?½`<0=\í \é¼\×\Â!½\Ñ=\ã=3<˜¼oF¾—«=\è]\'=j\Z½£~=‹L×¼\å <;Ç®»‹üZ= ‚˜=Eo4=\'è¼¿À’;?\ô<ûC=/KH=y2<e@½\ê\à\Z=\'\r½=\ÉY=K‘˜½‘üÃ½d ©=_ø~<\ÎZ½Nc=\æN\Ğ=´!½•x=@¼¢¦É¼\Èø!½\ÎOj=\Í\í#;\ÔzÉ½#FĞ»TJW½EÑ•½\\EÌ¼6gé¼Š¼\Õ!½\ô­u<‘\ó?½Cd	>a®=ûBÍ¼;‹;<ƒmR¼ª\ß½3P½š#=Ú„½²¨1:ØŒ‡=‰Y|;TŒ\ö»{ƒ\Å=\Ë\óC=Bù½\ïy½]}A=0\år¼6\à\Ö=«\ëf=3š¼Ë«C½½\ßÍ¼§]Æ¼€ü)<©½\Ä\Ê=Br\õ;!©½\Ş:—½\nj‚<¬‰º¹-½=ı™¼[â’½BÏ»\âÔ¾=\é(]¼²*€½\âI€³¿%«½\æÁ½\ñC\0¼‰û=„‡²=\È×½•ÿ½ \ó€=[¤½\êE³;ª\Ü<£½<\ZMš<‹ã ½G¼\æ¼y]œ<\íL½5(Š½)3¹½_!ù<P\Ë	<˜\ì+½›K›½\Ë}\è<\nv<ú^e¼‡0¼\ã²=Ud<]\ä`½Š	Y½¶3=«¬K:„]\è¼\è}ÿ·œ„O½‡A&=\õF<)>=–n\Ã<»ˆ£¼‚=«½[Â¢½+‡\î¼Kg5<zz¼¶¹Ñ½i½ŸP»\è–K½«%½\ğÑ»