 world and is one of the most helpful tool with which a hotel can understand more about its relationship with its guests. Letâ€™s move in deeper into the details of the final stage of guest check in. Upon clicking the â€˜Check-Inâ€™ button the above terminal is seen. The â€˜Enter Guest Informationâ€™ box is already filled by the system since the guest information was already saved during the creation of the reservation. To save the information, just click â€˜Add Guestâ€™. The system only lets the user check in a specified number of guests, which was entered at the time of saving the reservation hence it keeps count of the number of guests entered. If the number of guests entered equals to the number of guests specified, a prompt is generated to let the user know that the guest assignment has been completed and that the FIT check in process is complete. 3.1.1.2 Group Check In. Group check in is quite similar to FIT check in with minor difference. Below is a screen shot of the group check in module which can be accessed by',_binary '“NUMPY\0v\0{\'descr\': \'<f4\', \'fortran_order\': False, \'shape\': (384,), }                                                          \n\ßj\Ç=ı\ï¢<Èši½bCI=·ı)=•üL=T¡\Ç=İ£y½\Ï\É=Z\ğ¬<„T\Õ<)6É¼\ÄE<\â‰<=%Ø¼|³Ó½I/=³ş½ME=›\ç\ë<\ádH<`	½\Ø@ß¼¯2½Ÿ<¸<1è½ÿ§G=·«<6„†=)€½kM’¼X\Ş\Ê=W=\õS:=t=“Ş½\äŸH½»\ÚA½AÇœ¼\ÔÈº¸E½$å½UY½­|¢¼\ó1;£\Ó=³\r‡½\0K\Î<\ß¼sÖŠ=£C¢<™;V=‚r»<¢\Û<\ÓÆ¦¼U\Ê=“–1¼–e	½usÆ¼‚rĞ¼¬D”¼®\Èşºû»!\Ú¼\nh\'½\âx<½“p½®\Å¼ag¿=~ì½«‚¹¼‘Í=\Ñúª;#\İ\r¼\ê_o:\ï\ÙD½TP¼\Ê.«»g+ˆ=0Ï€½p)!½Q¿º\'Ê¬½+»¦»\õh;x\Ã<\Âú½y¹=\×\ó³;P½@\Í)¸&$=\ğ»U¼®\ìy¼t4O=Ä™#=”w½¡R6=?a\É=\\_\ô<\ó=\Ü\æŒ=\Ç:K½.¬T=\Ñù<MÁ¬½6\æ\Ø=\r\Â<$&:=JKV½\r±½²<\Ş;š\Ü	>üƒ\Ú;\ía½\×!¢=yr=£\÷‘=:øY<>½4!=¯ŒK¼cw <=_ø¼­Un½\İD½\ãbq=Õ¼\Ä	Ê‰£:•¿½™\Í$½kb	½¦™<\Ş¢½l„v½û\â<‘L-<s\r)¼t\Ô;<N3\ó½\\‹=u\âR½6ør¼\ä\Â=Z¼<Á\Í>5\İ=\ë=8=h=SÄ¼„_û<&­¥<³£‚=_%=o·\â¼j:T=:>‚»¸Hú¶Ç†½#%¼m\"—¼\Ñ3F¼ú==x–=\Ş\õR¼\' <Šù§¼\Z\Ú|½Å†½¦ƒ7½\É\n¥<¶Šˆ»\\XV½°À<	Wf½\İ‹<\ër=\ô\î=\É\Å½\Í\Öj=`„·½9c€<