e etc. The second one contains different room states as such Vacant, Out-of-order, Occupied etc. Selecting (Fig 2.5) different combinations of room states and room types and pressing the Find button or enter, the user can view the desired room having the selected states and types. For example in figure 2.2 and 2.3 user wishes to view all the single rooms in a hotel that are vacant. (Fig 2.5) Given below is a screen shot of the result where different room number and their corresponding states are seen. Fig (2.6) 2.2.7 View Room Button: In the above figure if one clicked room number 605 which is highlighted with the blue shade (indicating that the room is occupied), one would also be able to view the details of the room. The Figure is given below. 2.2.8 Reservation. Overview Fig (2.7) The figure above is from the Registration screen of the SDC. There are two types of reservations namely FIT Reservation and Group Reservation, which can be viewed by selecting the respective buttons shown below in figures 2.8 and 2.9. (FIT Reservation button or Group Reservation button). The result of the desired query can be seen',_binary '“NUMPY\0v\0{\'descr\': \'<f4\', \'fortran_order\': False, \'shape\': (384,), }                                                          \nF«—<-~v¼MY»½Áÿ§=’tt=\à¡\Ó=\ÏC<hV›½°9´=‹ÿ¼Z&O=x»^½l·½¾¼i¥2=\ñŠ`½\Ñ\n;jÍ‡½\ßü$<s 4<\É\Ö8<	{Â»r˜Á¼bbÂ¼\ôe¼\êaŸ<aY\Z½“ªM=Š\ó¼<ì·½ \Z\â<†¨µ=i+£=‰Cr=\ôA=F!½n\÷»\ë¼[\Õ=lù¼ˆ|r½u\"\Ò<Ğ¸Z¼F·»§½;ÿ\0<~½+l×¼u\ö0<\Ê={À=°\îP<ÁB½\ã’=^7ø<,±	>¬ƒÿ<f\ôÑ¼\×\Æ;]E\ß;\0*\Î<\Ê\Úl¼\ôœ<¨<›jL½+•=`ªÛ¼\äv=vÁ\';Ë¸-¾\\øŒ»\ê\ÆN<}0<<½\â\â\Ù<™—½7Ab½F¶ºq<‡\ñ½¾\Ü@½WJ=x*!¼v=˜›<^i˜<\çºE<ßœµ¼\àZ¹<\ÅÕ»F(Œ= \':•+¼\ÜÌ¼½k<P#:¼|B½ae=şÿ›=M\ä`¼”n1=ú´,=\ä\ôş<=¡¼Q_c<¿Î£½®\Æü=|\ß<A1\0½\Ã\çr»Ÿ´+½0r±=/¼%³¸½\ğÄ¢¼:@˜;ı,\é<\r»ÿ‡G=Z\ï.½\ğ—=\òq`¼dN¼:´g½\òK½·+u½\ÊH=Q\ãş	u¼&Ä–½#¢C½™Òª<\">\Ì&<\Â.¼\ĞÓ¸;\â_=o¬\Î<_e†<ı~œ=\ãš#½K ¥¼!¼\à2½ŒšJ¼Ö¸\ã=£bïº»†¦¼°&½©i(¼YY=\ÇÖ¼Á \Î=u^&>\ï_Ÿ=~\Ô=6\Ïû<s”;v;=™¡„»\ÕC=jc=Mù»<b{5=O