arge and VAT shown in the figure below. On the right hand corner of the screen the reservation details can be seen such as the check in date and the check out date and most importantly the payment method highlighted in bold. If the payment method is cash then the â€˜Cashâ€™ should be selected in the â€˜Payment Methodâ€™ box shown below. Since cash could be received in any currency that too should be documented by entering the right curreny in the next box together with the amount and press â€˜Enterâ€™. If the entered amount is less than the required amount then the system will generate a message prompting the user to enter more amount. If the amount entered is more than the required amount then the system will highlight the change that must be given back in NC. When all the monetary transactions are complete click the â€˜Acceptâ€™ button. Upon clicking the button a prompt is generated to confirm the check out of the guest from the hotel. Upon clicking â€˜Yesâ€™ the FIT is checked out of the system. Then the house keeping department is notified about the departure by changing the room status to â€˜Vacant â€“ Dirtyâ€™. 3.1.2.2 Group Check Out The screen above shows 3 rooms that are checking out and that all the three rooms belong to the same group. The method to access the check out screen is the same as FIT (by clicking â€˜Openâ€™ and then â€˜Settlementâ€™) but the screen can only be accessed through the group leaderâ€™s room which is highlighted in white (room 402). Below is the screen shot of the settlement window for group check out. The rates that are charged is automatically picked by the system which was chosen at the time of reservation. On the top right hand corner we can see the list of extra charges that needs to be settled before the check out procedure can be taken forward. The extra charges if present, can be settled is a very easy manner. Since the charges are posted in individuals of the group, they are the ones responsible for paying their extra charges. Therefore each of the rooms need to be selected from the â€˜Select Roomâ€™ box and',_binary '“NUMPY\0v\0{\'descr\': \'<f4\', \'fortran_order\': False, \'shape\': (384,), }                                                          \n†<>Û©=\Z6Ü½H×®¼€\Ş\÷<Æ¾==|=\Î$=®\Ê>=\Ó<KÄ°=\×À(½ù\Î\0=…¨¼#WŠ;n\é\õ½s¹7¼\éÁ†½66¾<u›\Û=•\È»¬\ÆT½`İ¼kS«»Ù>=\\ß®¼2´<¨O=\ò\é\ò¼‹)¥¼G\ÒI=¸\É\Î=¢x\Õ<\ö\Æ\÷¼$8	¼°`»\ÏU©¼D?•¼‹A\0½@H;g…“½±‡Á»\ó\Ìq=\ç½)½“¼‘=\÷½&;æ˜<’x2=\r®½¼8\Ñ=ş@\É<*5¤<\äa#;\÷k=²™f½Ü¤8=\ÏnE=1”\Ù<N½H½\È\âV½\åO\r»)$³<dH½\ZŞ«<®…+<d\\\Í<S<\Ó}!½#¢k»\ÈmÚ½>-;½·\ÍÊ¼¼\È@<Q”£½¼\Ñ\"½\ßi*º­*=\Ôÿ\ö<\ØJŸ<\Â\èĞ½°\æ™<úS=i)¼Ğ’¼\Çn=•²¼E5=M7½F¶ª8°á½\ó\İ\Ñ=˜DQ=*\æ½\í\ôQ½\â”=›\Z½Œm¶¼m¥=¸\Â>£<¡\ç\ê=Ö¹‡=!dÀ;6\ñ%=r¿\ë<*\\%¼s°=Ó‡=©ØŠ=\åh€½ò¡‡½F„=¯Ö =D\Å3½bG¼¹+=®—‡¼œ =3±=\Ôæ˜¼\Êú=\ä\è<mÿ	½`¢½;½aw&½\ô<l=<\Å	m\ÅÚ¼\'Û‚¼\ñ½Qm\"½\ğ~q=T`¼ˆ\òQ½=C‡=.Ê£=ZVK;”Y:½)/|;9½Y©½pI=\ï™¼³4¹=×¹<oK=ú\ã2<4©\r½\ôr¢=Û\ä<f$~=aw=“†&=…Fj=¡hœ½\ì\Åß¼OÕ£=\å¾½G\Èy<‡0<m\Ó\Ú< È€<\î2=+\Åİ¼\âL¼@3¾*½²™9<X\ô3=\Ö\Ê¼Ä±L½Pm=¯`¼2Õ¼[±=\ÒÎ«=\õ5†½0l»¼\éÈ¹½‹k»<‡†J½ÿ[¯½v\õ‰<›h!<”ı\ä¼\óş=À”;ƒ³€½\Ô\å	½\å6½ [È½ß·d=N¤¼Z^•½§C^=™T¨¼©R½¢p¨=Is\ó=©j=Z\Õv< w\ö<˜”¼)\ôs<%q\ô¼\ÚØ¼£«É½n\ì^=\'\öe¼¸\Ş= Se½ Jø¼0\ô¨=,\Ü\"½”=¦½Š\ì½oku¼\nù$=\í\ê\n;Ì…«=–‚\î‰\És¼\ÍÙ›<•6½¹LŠ½j%—¼M¶Q=L´^;Ì®V¼^=\İH\Ö<’+‡½\å–ï¼¯À6<\èfk½d:D½:Œ\Í<\nù@<\ÔUˆ½\÷¹¼Nc»=\ÍzÁ<Áˆ<“\İh¼Á$û<1¼ş<J\ŞP=`\Ã=v½\×IŒ½‰§¼\ï	=\Ó\Ñ½]Z¡½?Vy=uÈ¼™Ñ½\åO&=nÀC=µü½X¨=­Ï£:‰\"\Ø<;\"—½§k=[U»bv½\Şwß»©…ğ¼²Š“<\Ó@/½vA-<\áb½À\" <¤e…<—R“½’>~+†=^î°¼³\×_½t\ó)¼¥ Õ¼\î\íÀ¼\Û\È<;j7=\n\Ò½™€e<B\ï»;%fºü¡•=/–\Û<\è»\ï½\\xÛ½±K=\å¼sœK=\'¢¦<a =ş§ï½•´¼\ô£¨¼b\ä»·½\\}ü<~€¼\Ò\Ín½a\Òê¼¾´U»Ñ˜ ½&a½b –½\é\Ôb½2®¸C\îK<U¾\ö¼şª<½\ã|†³pN²½¶¢q½§…;\Âo=$;=&¦Û½xœ¼	uC=€­^½3•+¼ˆ­¼ú\Æ\Ñ;®‚½\Ô\ìË½¨\'\ë¹?\ì<\ö˜½\Ğ\ï<¸_¿½™•=\Ø$<\é6›¼\ÏÂ½\ÊI\Ä:\Õ\í»s\nÕ»be½\×N$>9ª<ÀVŒ<Fÿ<\ò0\â=¦b\ê:@“½”6½¦\ì<Û˜=\á¯\Ö<@\äa=TS\è=MS ;‘Ê½Ó™`½1P\ô<\ò\Ó\0=Õ‰G»[”c½{¿Z¼m¼Ö˜Ì½K\é\í¼R#½ÿ\ØX=ŠÁ\Í<­Ê»V&5¼\"·\î<\Æ&=§ü„=’X=¿”œ¼2Ù»\é‰B=ùƒ;½','b02fb4d5-15f0-4a5e-9fc4-63cb0767009e'),(3170,'61b765e5-ae10-4594-beff-e88be67efe3c',10,'taken forward. The extra charges if present, can be settled is a very easy manner. Since the charges are posted in individuals of the group, they are the ones responsible for paying their extra charges. Therefore each of the rooms need to be selected from the â€˜Select Roomâ€™ box and their individual bills need to be settled. After entering the payment method and the amount press â€˜Enterâ€™ to save the information. If there is another room with an extra charge posted to it then it can also be selected from the â€˜Select Roomâ€™ box following the same procedure of settlement explained above. When the required amount has been entered and also all the extra charges have been settled click â€˜Settle Billâ€™. A prompt is generated to confirm the action. After clicking â€˜Yesâ€™ the bills are settled and now the check out procedure can be initiated. To go ahead with the check out procedure the billing instruction needs to be checked. If the billing instruction says â€˜Bill to Travel Agentâ€™ then â€˜TA Voucherâ€™ should be selected as the Payment Method. If â€˜Payment at Check Outâ€™ is the billing instruction then the amount, currency and mode (cash/credit card) needs to be entered. When the parameters entered are accepted by the system click â€˜Check-Out Groupâ€™ button. Upon clicking â€˜Yesâ€™ at the prompt the group is successfully checked out of the system and out of the hotel. 3.2 Point of Sale Functions 3.2.1 Start a Table The figure above is a screen shot of the main screen of the POS. The numbers on each of the green buttons represent a table number and the color represents its present state. To start a table one must click on the respective table where the current state is vacant. Upon clicking any of the vacant tables a prompt is generated for the server/manager password. After entering the passwords the system asks for the total number of guests being served on that table. Upon entering the required information and pressing â€˜Okâ€™, the ordering panel becomes available from where we can select the items that were ordered by the guest. After the ordering is complete the kitchen is to be notified hence the â€˜Sendâ€™ button needs to be clicked for the order to be sent to the kitchen. Below is a screen shot of the ordering panel. When the â€˜Sendâ€™ button is clicked, a printer placed in the kitchen prints the KOTâ€™s together with all the information such as the table number, ordering server, order time and order details in that KOT. The table status also changes from vacant to occupied. 3.2.2 Add more items to an existing Table To add more items to an existing table just click on the respective table to open it. When the ordering screen is screen after entering the right server password, select the items being ordered just as before by clicking their names on the screen and when youâ€™re done click â€˜Sendâ€™ for the kitchen to be notified. 3.2.3 Settle a Table',_binary '“NUMPY\0v\0{\'descr\': \'<f4\', \'fortran_order\': False, \'shape\': (384,), }                                                          \n\è\ák<7\á=\Ãxz½_<¼±¼\0Q¯»\Ì\Ë=\ïÂ¼™QQ=^(=\n|¹=) §½\Zz«<¨\"¼rf =–¬Ä½\åŒ2¼\ó­½°Á½½.l=~Jª»Q@¼lµ\\¼(t(½©#Î»\Ë$9¼††ü;[‘ºH7£<4\"+½•…=±\Ô\à=\Zd\Ü<\Óo„½\Ô\ô==\ñ\î\ë;\ó”¼Gk½kl—¼¢\è]<³\'½ÍŒ!½\ğ‹;\n\Çy½²\ôy=t[¥<\Ï\ã¼\çhp=ËŠ¼0\é}=£\Óf=\í8\í¼‘$<Q\Ò?=úÓ‘½I+‰;\è–=ƒ/¼Y:Q0ê½¼^L½º[ÿ<Š”J½,\İ0=E„½+\ÒL=\Å5\Í:ü8\n=U<WøP½E1\ë<E>=<sÈ=¹¬¼š¼¿9\í°=r\È¹\íZp9\Í=t’»\Ï\÷\Ë<¨\ã,½ü‘½Ö«›»5	„<`=½t\É½\Ôtüº—\ë\é;šc½\ğı= \Ö=¼);ˆø›½Äªª=\n\Ë9{½lŠn¼DÜ–=\0‘\Ñ:1F€=‘o\Ï<e@Ù¼^/½D\ä=O\n©¼Nt\Å=\î\è;8˜=\ñ$T½±>T½ Ld½?¸=‹\à½I½z­\ë=zK\È<Ø—c<Á=9®‡½q$F=s%=”~½\÷dº½*//=ƒ\"G=]\ß,=\àË›	\Şo¼|\r¡¼şøl½Y½û©=\ßC\n½\Õdß¼\õ\ÛU=À\ğ¿¼\ŞU\Z=\Â4Š¼OJÙ½\ñ5=\ê}½¥ˆ±½)\Ä9R\r½ı\ëC=”‹¼¸Cø=3\Ó;*Ë»pÀµ= À§=û‘N½ù\Æü=œ„¶<\òI«<t\à\å<j…¼X¡;=©q¶<úQ£<¾x¯=Û¯N½\â\ê¸=\å\Ú\Ù<\ód;q\ÄW=<\r1½²\ÌO¼.Ç¼\àw\ğ<(—†¼”\×7½r/H=®\äx¼9½1È=\ö’\Â=‡–€½KPR<e¿Ô½d\ì~»\õş\n½\ñfÃ½·º¼\÷\óG¼¡3­;0\Û^½~‰\Ù;\\e¶½„